Guide/anbsp;nbsp;a class="button-fancy" href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/guides/book_a_server"i class="fa-solid fa-server"/inbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Booking an au.serveme.tf server/anbsp;nbsp;a class="button-fancy" href="https://discord.com/channels/949522376297701396/1073914845650493530"i class="fa-solid fa-server"/inbsp;nbsp;nbsp;Booking a Rhizome server/a/div

---

### Welcome back!
We're back, with a new season naming scheme! There's a bit that we've changed based off of your feedback of Sixes Season 37, and we hope you are excited for Sixes Spring '23 (S38)! In the off-season, we ran our second iteration of the Experimental Cup series, namely Experimental Cup 2. The feedback of the Progressive Ruleset / Pro Ruleset Timer plugin we tested in that tournament will directly impact Sixes Spring '23 (S38).

### Signups
You can sign up for Sixes Spring '23 (S38) from **Sunday the 24th of September**, up until **Wednesday the 4th of October 2023**. We aim to have seeding out by **Friday the 6th of October, if not Saturday the 7th of October at the latest**, before the season starts. The season starts **Sunday the 8th of October 2023**.

**Please see the signup agreement at the bottom of the page for further information on helping us out with seedings!**

#### Staff Updates
We are sad to announce that frydog and snazzy will be departing from the Sixes roster, but we wish them the best of luck in their futures, and would like to thank them for their many contributions in the short time they were working with us! We would also like to welcome **wils** to the team, who will be jumping into the Sixes League Admin role to round out our team for the season!

![](https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1154969482717040670/1162346795540680774/Prizepool_Sixes.jpg)

### Prize Pool for Sixes Spring '23
We are excited to announce a prize pool for the Premier division of Sixes Spring '23! This season will feature a $600 AUD prize pool to be spilt between the top three placing Premier teams. The distribution will be as follows:

 1. $360
 2. $180
 3. $60

A thank you to multi for donating $300, and to all of our Patrons, past and present, who helped us match this donation.

---

div class="news-container"div class="panel-group" id="accordion"div class="panel panel-default"div class="panel-heading"h3 class="panel-title" id="news-title"a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse_news2" class="news-link"Sixes Spring '23 (S38) changesnbsp;nbsp;i class="fa-solid fa-caret-down"/i/a/h3/divdiv id="collapse_news2" class="panel-collapse collapse"div class="panel-body"ppulliThe Loch-n-Load is now banned./li
liThe Detonator and the Gas Passer have been unbanned./li
liThe Sniper class limit has been reduced to 1./li
liThe Progressive Ruleset Timer will be implemented across all divisions. You can read more about how it works a href="https://ozfortress.com/leagues/56"here/a./li
liThe Map Timer on Control Point maps has been reduced to 25 minutes./li
liPremier will feature a bottom four playoff bracket./li/ul
For a full list of changes affecting Spring '23 seasons, see the news post a href="https://ozfortress.com/forums/threads/1278"here/a/p/p/div/div/div/div/div

---

div class="news-container"div class="panel-group" id="accordion"div class="panel panel-default"div class="panel-heading"h3 class="panel-title" id="news-title"a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse_news7" class="news-link"Signup Agreementnbsp;nbsp;i class="fa-solid fa-caret-down"/i/a/h3/divdiv id="collapse_news7" class="panel-collapse collapse"div class="panel-body"
pBy signing up, you acknowledge that byou may be placed in any division/b the badministrators deem fit/b for your roster, and thus byour entire team should be reasonable in their expectations on division placement/b. We will endeavour to let teams know of changes in initial seedings before the final release. Please ensure you bspecify the division you truly believe your team should be in/b, this will make it easier for administrators to consult with you on your seeding. Along with selecting your desired division, please also blist who you expect to play, and what class/role/b. We've left a template below, please include it in your signup application's description./p
code
Scout: br
Scout: br
Soldier: br
Soldier: br
Demoman: br
Medic: 
/code
hr
pbPlease also add your captains' discord handles to the bottom. We will be displaying these on team pages going forward. Your roster should have at minimum two captains./b/p
/div/div/div/div/div

---

div class="news-container"div class="panel-group" id="accordion"div class="panel panel-default"div class="panel-heading"h3 class="panel-title" id="news-title"a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse_news8" class="news-link"How to; Create a Team, Join a Team, and Sign up!nbsp;nbsp;i class="fa-solid fa-caret-down"/i/a/h3/divdiv id="collapse_news8" class="panel-collapse collapse"div class="panel-body"
pOn the ozfortress website, captains can create Teams using the "Start Team" button on the Teams page. Once created, captains can invite players to the team. Team invites are shown on a player's profile, which can be accessed by clicking on your name next to the bell on the top right-hand corner of your screen. Teams provide a pool of players that can be signed up for a tournament. Players may be in the pool for multiple teams but only one active roster for any given tournament. Captains may sign up a roster for tournaments under the league page./p

pIf you're new and not sure how to get started, don't fret! Check out the Recruitment category of the a href="https://discord.gg/dyudcxB"ozfortress Discord/a where you can express your interest in joining a team, or peruse potential players to form a team of your own. Sixes teams are comprised of two scouts, two soldiers, one demo and one medic. If you're new to the competitive scene, a href="https://docs.ozfortress.com/guides/newbie_guide"click here/a for an introduction to ozfortress!/p

pOnce you've signed up your team or have joined one, your part is done. Don't worry if you didn't find or join a team in time, you can always be transferred onto a team in one of the Transfer Windows. See the Transfers link for more info on Transfers, and the Transfers Window link for info on when these windows are, both links can be found at the bottom./p

pbPlease ensure you have enough backups to last the entire season/b; teams are allowed a maximum of ten (10) players rostered./p

/div/div/div/div/div

---

### Reminders

 - During Sixes Spring '23 (S38) we plan on conducting random demo checks to ensure players are recording POV demos. Please ensure that you are recording match demos in order to avoid punishment.
 - If you are unsure of whether or not something is considered a game exploit, contact a League Administrator for clarification. Ignorance is not an excuse.

---

